programmes.show_description: Programmes Start at 07:00
Happy Hedgie Halloween: Pins and Nettie are two little hedgehogs who usually love to go out and explore.
It's Time to be a Super Hero: When JoJo and Gran Gran visit the library, Terrence is about to launch a new Super Saleem book at a special story event later.
It's Time to Play Beach Cricket: JoJo and her family are ready for an exciting day on the beach playing cricket, but Auntie Dee hasn't packed the wickets. Luckily, Gran Gran has a plan!
The friends learn the value of respecting nature when some of their insect guests refuse to check into their new bug hotel.
Cuán feels pressured to create the perfect picture for Pip's art display, until an unexpected adventure with his friends shows him that inspiration often comes from having fun.
Fun and games with the animals of the forest.
Spoiling The Ambatsador: Adam asks Shelby to fly upside down so their bat guest, who lives hanging from the ceiling, can feel at home. But now the crew can't reach the controls!
Bounced: The team lands on a squishy, blob-covered planet - only to discover the planet might be alive... and doesn't want them to leave.
When Doodle Girl's fun beach day gets interrupted by wave-making Merdogs, she dives into a doodle-filled adventure under the sea to help calm their grumpy king and save the shore!
The Growing Potion: Spin finds his favourite socks under his bed, but they're too small for him. The Mixmups mix up an adventure to find a way to grow them big again.
Juno Mama Day: Juno can't wait for Juno-Mama Day, but Mama gets a cold. Vida teaches Juno to be a junior nurse instead!
Tidbit's Thirsty Day: When Tidbit gets dehydrated, Vida helps him find a way to play AND hydrate at the same time.
Groom Ba: When their barber goes on vacation ahead of Robotics Team picture day, the Dream Factory Crew build a grooming robot to get themselves ready for their close-up.
Leon Look-Alike: The Dream Factory Crew, Carlos and his pet cockatiel, Leon, make new friends when another cockatiel flies into the Dream Factory and their adventures begin.
Mandy and Sarah are making a film comparing dogs and cats, and the cats are clearly winning until a kitchen fire gives Nipper a chance to shine.
At a picnic on Annie's farm, Peter comes up with a series of games that almost lead to disaster. Meanwhile, Lizzie and Jodie search for a rare seal.
Zoom wants to find out if Mark and Amy can make plastic out of milk. The children bury plastic and food in soil. And they end up on a plastic-free shopping trip!! (SL)
Zoom finds out why bogs are superheroes of planet earth. Amy and Mark test how good moss is at soaking up water and Mark takes Zoom to the biggest bog in Ireland. (SL)

A journey back 65 million years to the time of the Tyrannosaurus Rex and its existence in North America.
